	</tr>
	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				The plague sharks are roughly level 30. I wouldnt suggest trying to solo one. At all. Not unless you are above 45. They have a really nasty, fast bite that has an effect of dispell. Bye bye buffs. They also have some pathing problems. Enduring breath is a requirement. If you surface for air, they seem to teleport WAY away from you. We lost a couple this way. They also don't like getting to close to shore. Again, they teleport And for whatever reason the don't come back in either case. Don't get too close to the shipwreck either. More pathing trouble there. Get your Ranger buddy to help you out with thier tracking(thanks Eshkin!) because finding out that the shark that you were trying to target is a Killer shark is not fun. They can see you before you can see them when submerged. And the bug that allows you to see everything underwater works but you can't target diddly in this zone with that trick.<BR>
<BR>
And those killer sharks are trouble. The killers will eat the plagues,... and you. Blue to a 41 (barely) but nasty nasty nasty. We had a party that had 34 pal, 35 pal, 36 wiz, 41 ranger and we lost a fight. We didnt kill the one that we fought because a second showed. Not 100% positive we would've killed the first one without party losses though. Woulda been a lot better with a healer but...<BR>
<BR>
There is a pathing bug that you can use to your advantage. The boat that comes in from Qeynos will sometimes pick up an NPC and bring it close to shore. If it is a plague, it will actaully try to beach itself to the left of the dock as you are looking out from the island, right at a little point of land, about half way to the corner of the island.  If you stay in the water right here and the plague is the one that the boat is picking up, it will go agro on you. Try to kill whatever the boat is picking up if it is not a plague. Not a reliable bug but it could help you.<BR>
<BR>
The biggest key to these things is STAY UNDER THE WATER during the fighting. Surfacing will make the shark run. Beaching will make the shark run. Spells against the shark or benifiting you will only work when everyone involved is totaly submerged. You cannot have a nuker or healer on the beach and a group underwater fighting. I even had a LoH fail because I was on the beach trying to heal someone trying to make it to shore. Got the &quot;he was protected&quot; message.<BR>
<BR>
Hope this helps. <BR>
<BR>
Gorindell Stoutheart , 34th Paladin<BR>
Order of the Phoenix<BR>
Prexus
				</font>
			</td>

	</tr>
	
